                            <comment id="14298841" author="stack" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2015 16:45:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. We&apos;ve talked of doing this for a long time.  I was hoping the new API would make this effort easier to do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14298987" author="ndimiduk" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2015 18:13:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now that we have abstractions at the client-api level, I think the limiting factor is the map reduce code for writing HFiles. As &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; commented in the thread you linked, we should have a separate hbase-storage module that both a hbase-server and hbase-mapreduce modules can depend upon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
